    waypoint_navgoal_1:form =
    {
      help = "===========DESCRIPTION============================"$0D"A waypoin"
       "t for script navgoals, 1 x 1 size. Not included in navigation data."$0D
       "===========SPAWNFLAGS============================="$0D"SOLID_OK - only"
       " use if placing inside solid is unavoidable in map, but may be clear i"
       "n-game (i.e.: at the bottom of a tall, solid lift that starts at the t"
       "op position)."$0D"===========KEYS&VALUES============================"$0D
       "'targetname' - Name you would use in script when setting a navgoal. (S"
       "ee notes.)"$0D"==============NOTES==============================="$0D"F"
       "or example: if you give this waypoint a targetname of 'console', make "
       "an NPC go to it in a script like so:"$0D"set ('navgoal', 'console');"$0D
       "You CANNOT set a radius on these navgoals, they are touch-reach ONLY."$0D
       "Navigation Goals should be off the main waypoint network. They must ha"
       "ve a clear path to at least one waypoint. These are specific destinati"
